LICENSE — TO BE CHOSEN BEFORE PUBLICATION
=========================================

No open-source license has been selected for this project yet. Until a license
is chosen and added here, **all rights are reserved** and the contents must not
be treated as freely reusable.

Recommended options (decide per the project's goals):

  - Software (iOS app, firmware):   MIT  or  Apache-2.0
  - Hardware (CAD, 3D-print files):  CERN-OHL-S/-W  or  CC-BY-4.0 / CC-BY-SA-4.0
  - Documentation:                   CC-BY-4.0

Note: a dual approach (software under MIT/Apache, hardware under CERN-OHL or
CC-BY-SA) is common for projects that ship both code and physical designs.

PATENTS: the pedal-control method (head-angle threshold + press speed) is patented
in Japan -- JP 6726319 B2 "Auxiliary pedal system" and JP 7004771 B2 "Device
controller"; priority-basis PCT (English): WO 2019/176164. Patent licensing
generally depends on the counterparty's intended embodiment, BUT for genuinely
public/open-purpose uses the authors intend to grant a licence FREE OF CHARGE.
In particular, for products or services that help people with disabilities (and
others who need it) participate in society more inclusively -- even commercial,
paid ones -- bFaaaP-related patent licensing is, as a matter of policy, granted
FREE OF CHARGE. Contact Tomoyuki Shishido (https://bfaaap.com ; ORCID
0000-0002-8944-2088). For software reuse, also prefer a licence with an explicit
PATENT GRANT (e.g. Apache-2.0). See README (Patents) and PUBLISHING-CHECKLIST.md.

Third-party components retain their own licenses and are NOT relicensed:
  - firmware/libraries/iq-module-communication-arduino/  → see its LICENSE file
  - Motor datasheets (motor/) are vendor copyright — referenced, not redistributed.

